                                                        Definition of simulation                                
        
                
                
                                                    

                    
              
              
              3a
                  
            
          
            
                                                : the imitative representation of the functioning of one system or process by means of the functioning of another                                      
             
             a computer simulation of an industrial process         
      

        

                
      
              b
                  
            
          
            
                                                : examination of a problem often not subject to direct experimentation by means of a simulating device                                      
      

        

                
  
            
                    
                
                
                        
                
                
                
                    
                            
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                

                        
                        
                                                    
                        Examples of simulation in a Sentence
                                                                                                            
                                                                                                
    
    
    
                            


          
         
                        a computer simulation of spaceflight    
  
                        


          
         
                        a simulation of the planet's surface    
  
                                                                                                                                                                  

                                                            See More
    
        
            
            
        
    

    
        
            
            
        
    

                        
                                                                                                    
                            
                                                                                                            Recent Examples on the Web

    
        In 2012, eight years after his fiancee Jessica Pereira died of a rare disease at age 23, Joshua Barbeau created an AI simulation of her.
        
        	—
        	
            Cheri Lucas Rowlands, Longreads, 21 Sep. 2021        	
        
    
    
        The last release of EA's college football simulation was also its best.
        
        	—
        	
            Brett Molina, USA TODAY, 19 Aug. 2021

                                                            See More
    
        
            
            
        
    

    
        
            
            
        
    

                                                                        
                
                                                                        
                        First Known Use of simulation
                                                    14th century, in the meaning defined at sense 1                                            
                
                                                                                              
                    
                        History and Etymology for simulation
                                                    
                        
                Middle English simulacion, from Anglo-French, from Latin simulation-, simulatio, from simulare

                                                        Legal Definition of simulation                                
        
                
                
                                                    

                    
              

            in the civil law of Louisiana        
          
  
              
              1
                  
            
          
            
                                                : the act of simulating                                      
      

        

                
  
              
              2
                  
            
          
            
                                                : a contract that by mutual agreement does not express the true intent of the parties  — see also counterletter  — compare disguised donation at donation                                      
                

  Note:
            Although a simulation does not have effect as between the parties, its lack of effect may not be asserted against third parties, such as creditors or bona fide purchasers, to avoid liability.
